quantreg -- Quantile Regression (Version 3.01)

This is a new version of the quantile regression software for Splus.
There is a parallel version for R also available at the web site.

Initially it is available for Splus 5.1 for Unix, and with some luck
it will eventually be made available for Splus 3.x for Unix, Splus 5.1
for linux, and perhaps even for various windows versions of Splus.
See the file S2R for some comments on the differences between the
S and R versions.

This version incorporates the algorithmic developments reported in
Portnoy and Koenker (1997, Statistical Science) as well as a number
of other modernizations.  Foremost among the latter is the that
the transition to the lm() formula specification of the linear model
has been made.  I hope that this will make the function substantially
easier to use.  There are also a number of new developments for
inference.  Further developments are anticipated. 

The archive consists of the following pieces:

	rq.q		a file containing all the s functions
	rqbr.r		a ratfor file with the original simplex algorithm
	rqfn.r		a ratfor file with the new interior point algorithm
	xlapack.f	a fortran file with some "extra" lapack routines
				needed for the rqfn algorithm.
	help.d		a directory with  documentation files in 3.x  style
				These files were automatically translated
				from the sgm by sgml2roff.
	help.sgm	a directory with  documentation files in 5.x  style
	README		this file
	INSTALL		some notes on installation
	S2R		file with some comments about differences between the
				R and S versions of the package.


